e high coalescence rate, prevalence of very\nhigh-eccentricity orbits, and gravitational radiation ``spikes'' during close\nencounters in our runs, may provide interesting signals for the future Laser\nInterferometer Space Antenna (LISA).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Dec 2006 22:31:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 2 Mar 2007 17:58:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
